#### Example 4.4

Sketch the output currents of a differential pair in response to changes in the device width and the tail current.

#### Solution

Consider the characteristic depicted in Figure 4.14(a). As \(W / L\) grows, \(\Delta V_{i n 1}\) diminishes, shrinking the input range where both devices remain active [Figure 4.14(b)]. As \(I_{S S}\) increases, both the input range and the output current range expand [Figure 4.14(c)]. Intuitively, we anticipate the circuit to become more linear as \(I_{S S}\) increases or \(W / L\) decreases.

